const faqs = [
  { q: 'Is the MX Anywhere 3S worth it over the MX Anywhere 3?', a: 'Yes, if you value silent clicks or work on glass. The 3S adds 90% quieter clicks and an 8000 DPI Darkfield sensor that tracks on glass — two upgrades the older Anywhere 3 lacks. If you already own the Anywhere 3 and use a desk pad, the upgrade is harder to justify because the shape, weight, and scroll wheel are essentially identical.' },
  { q: 'How does the MX Anywhere 3S compare to the MX Master 3S?', a: 'The Anywhere 3S is the travel-sized sibling. It uses the same Darkfield sensor, the same silent clicks, and the same MagSpeed scroll mechanism, but in a 99-gram body that is roughly two-thirds the size. The trade-offs are comfort and buttons: no thumb wheel, only 4 programmable buttons, and the smaller shape fatigues large hands. Pick the Master 3S for a desk, the Anywhere 3S for travel.' },
